                        <span class="text">
                            <a href="/batteries/applications/recreational-vehicles">
                                Recreational Vehicles
                            </a>
                        </span>

                        <div class="mobile-subnav-arrow">
                            <div class="icon icon-arrow-down"></div>
                            <div class="icon icon-arrow-up"></div>
                        </div>
                    </li>

        </ul>


    </div>

            <div class="reg-text-header">
        <h1>Batteries for Passenger Vehicles</h1>
    </div>
    <div class="container content-text page-sub">
        <p>Passenger vehicle powertrains are becoming increasingly diverse as vehicle technology evolves to meet fuel-efficiency and carbon-emission regulations. But these vehicles all have one thing in common: a need for durable, high-performance batteries. We offer a full portfolio of batteries to meet the needs of passenger vehicles &mdash; from internal combustion engines to fully electric vehicles</p>
    </div>



    <div class="revised-image-callout-right revised-image-callout revised-callout-wrapper container">

        <div class="category col-sm-12">

        </div>
        <div class="col-sm-6">
                <div class="image">
                    <img src='/-/media/jci/ps/applications/images/ps_page_icevehicles.jpg' alt='page_icevehicles' />
                </div>
            <div class="youtube-video-control">



            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="col-sm-6">

            <div class="revised-callout-content">
                    <div class="content-title">
                        Internal Combustion Engine Vehicles
                    </div>

                    <div class="content-text">
                        <p>Vehicles powered by internal combustion engines represent the majority of the automotive market. They use lead-acid batteries to start the vehicle and power accessories. These batteries need to be reliable and, as electrical systems become more demanding, increasingly durable.&nbsp;</p>
<p>View our products for internal combustion engine vehicles:</p>
<ul>
    <li><a href="/batteries/lead-acid-batteries/flood-lead-acid-batteries">Standard flooded batteries</a></li>
    <li><a href="/batteries/lead-acid-batteries/enhanced-flooded-batteries">Enhanced flooded batteries</a> (EFB)</li>
    <li><a href="/batteries/lead-acid-batteries/aborbent-glass-mat-batteries">Absorbent glass mat batteries</a> (AGM)</li>
</ul>
                    </div>

                <div class="content-btns">

                </div>

            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="pin"></div>
    </div>



    <div class="revised-image-callout-right revised-image-callout revised-callout-wrapper container">

        <div class="category col-sm-12">

        </div>
        <div class="col-sm-6">
                <div class="image">
                    <img src='/-/media/jci/ps/applications/images/ps_page_startstop.jpg' alt='page_startstop' />
                </div>
            <div class="youtube-video-control">



            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="col-sm-6">

            <div class="revised-callout-content">
                    <div class="content-title">
                        Start Stop Vehicles
                    </div>

                    <div class="content-text">
                        <p>Start-stop vehicles use internal combustion engines that automatically shut off when the car is idling, then restart when the driver&rsquo;s foot leaves the brake pedal. When the engine is off, the vehicle&rsquo;s electrical system uses energy from the battery. The battery is used to restart the engine after each stopping event. Start-stop vehicles provide up to 5 percent more fuel-efficiency and reduced CO2 emissions.&nbsp;</p>
<p>View our products for start-stop vehicles:</p>
<ul>
    <li><a href="/batteries/lead-acid-batteries/enhanced-flooded-batteries">Enhanced flooded batteries</a> (EFB)</li>
    <li><a href="/batteries/lead-acid-batteries/aborbent-glass-mat-batteries">Absorbent glass mat batteries</a> (AGM)</li>
</ul>
<p><a href="/batteries/applications/passenger-vehicles/start-stop-vehicles">Learn more about start-stop technology.</a></p>
                    </div>

                <div class="content-btns">

                </div>

            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="pin"></div>
    </div>



    <div class="revised-image-callout-right revised-image-callout revised-callout-wrapper container">

        <div class="category col-sm-12">

        </div>
        <div class="col-sm-6">
                <div class="image">
                    <img src='/-/media/jci/ps/applications/images/ps_page_advancedstartstop.jpg' alt='page_advancedstartstop' />
                </div>
            <div class="youtube-video-control">



            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="col-sm-6">

            <div class="revised-callout-content">
                    <div class="content-title">
                        Advanced Start-Stop Vehicles
                    </div>

                    <div class="content-text">
                        <p>Advanced start-stop vehicles further enhance fuel efficiency through added capabilities such as engine-off coasting, electric boost and regenerative braking. These vehicles are 5&ndash;8 percent more efficient that internal combustion engine powered vehicles, and help automakers meet stringent fuel efficiency regulations without major changes to conventional powertrains and electrical systems. Advanced start-stop vehicles use two batteries, a 12 volt lead-acid battery and a 12 volt lithium-ion battery.<br>
<br>
View our products for advanced start-stop vehicles:</p>
<ul>
    <li><a href="/batteries/lithium-ion-batteries">12-volt lithium-ion battery</a></li>
</ul>
                    </div>

                <div class="content-btns">

                </div>

            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="pin"></div>
    </div>



    <div class="revised-image-callout-right revised-image-callout revised-callout-wrapper container">

        <div class="category col-sm-12">

        </div>
        <div class="col-sm-6">
                <div class="image">
                    <img src='/-/media/jci/ps/applications/images/ps_page_microhybrid.jpg' alt='page_microhybrid' />
                </div>
            <div class="youtube-video-control">



            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="col-sm-6">

            <div class="revised-callout-content">
                    <div class="content-title">
                        Micro-Hybrid Vehicles
                    </div>

                    <div class="content-text">
                        <p>These vehicles extend start-stop functionality even further. They use two batteries: a 12 volt lead-acid battery starts the engine and powers accessories; a 48 volt lithium-ion battery captures power from regenerative braking and powers high-load functions such as electric air conditioning, active chassis technology, and an electric traction motor that supplements the internal combustion engine to propel the vehicle. Micro-hybrid vehicles are 12&ndash;15 percent more efficient than &nbsp;conventional internal combustion engine powered vehicles.&nbsp;</p>
<p>View our products for micro-hybrid vehicles:</p>
<ul>
    <li><a href="/batteries/lithium-ion-batteries">48 volt lithium-ion battery</a></li>
</ul>
                    </div>

                <div class="content-btns">

                </div>

            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="pin"></div>
    </div>



    <div class="revised-image-callout-right revised-image-callout revised-callout-wrapper container">

        <div class="category col-sm-12">

        </div>
        <div class="col-sm-6">
                <div class="image">
                    <img src='/-/media/jci/ps/applications/images/ps_page_hybridelectric.jpg' alt='page_hybridelectric' />
                </div>
            <div class="youtube-video-control">



            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="col-sm-6">

            <div class="revised-callout-content">
                    <div class="content-title">
                        Hybrid Electric Vehicles
                    </div>

                    <div class="content-text">
                        <p>Hybrid electric vehicles (HEVs) are powered by both an internal combustion engine and a high-voltage electric battery that is recharged by the internal combustion engine. HEVs are 20&ndash;40 percent more efficient than conventional vehicles powered by an internal combustion engine alone, and are an important part of the solution to meet longer-term fuel efficiency and admissions regulations without compromising vehicle range. HEVs use two batteries, a 12 volt lead-acid battery and a high-voltage lithium-ion battery.</p>
<p>View our products for hybrid electric vehicles:</p>
<ul>
    <li><a href="/batteries/lithium-ion-batteries">High-voltage lithium-ion battery</a></li>
</ul>
                    </div>

                <div class="content-btns">

                </div>

            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="pin"></div>
    </div>







        


